- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper analyzes Twitter data to understand the public debate on gun control.
- cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) is also likely as the paper focuses on public opinion and discourse surrounding a political issue.
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is a possible category as the paper uses natural language processing techniques to analyze the content of tweets.
- cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy) is a possible category as the paper may touch on issues related to online privacy and security in the context of social media data analysis.
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is a possible category as the paper uses computational methods to analyze a social issue.
